ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would absolutely recommend it. It is a lot of work but very interesting and nothing too stressful or challenging because the workload is broken up into so many parts.

it's a good class to get your feet wet and to take in a lot under a little time. Once you take this class, you should be identify your areas of interest. I would recommend taking this class if you enjoy taking tests and if you dislike class participation, since you do a lot of the former and not so much of the latter.
I would recommend this as an undergraduate course but not as a graduate course.
I would make sure that my fellow student was aware that the course is basically an undergrad lecture. If he/she was aware of that and still interested, I would recommend it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It is completely unrelated to what I am studying but very interesting material to learn about.
I have no prior knowledge of this field, but this class really interests me.
It filled in some of the gaps I had about the thinking area in general and gave me some research ideas for future research.
I learned to be more detail-oriented in this course.
It has allowed me to be more conscious about how people think
This course helped broaden my knowledge of cognitive psychology, which is not my main area.
